	<title>Accso Workshop 2018: Digitalisierung braucht neue Architekturen</title>
	<presentation id="index">
		<title>API Economy: Who is in the Driver's Seat?</title>
		<toc class="abstract">The term "API Economy" is frequently used, but in most cases it may turn out to be a misnomer. While some organizations indeed primarily make money with and through APIs, most do not. It thus may make more sense to think about "API Economics", which could be defined as an analysis of how APIs factor into an organization's business model. Armed with this new perspective of looking at business first and APIs second, some of the common trends and expectations may look a little less dazzling, but on the other hand a bit more realistic.</toc>
		<author><a href="http://dret.net/netdret/">Erik Wilde</a> <a href="http://twitter.com/dret" class="twitter-follow-button" data-size="large" title="Erik Wilde on Twitter: @dret">(<code>@dret</code>)</a></author>
